The paper discusses the use of neuromorphic hardware for implementing low-latency, energy-efficient accelerators for machine learning applications, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of backpropagation for training the lpRNN cell, which is a common technique used in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the advantages of using low pass filters as temporal regularizers, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the lpRNN cell in ultra-low power edge computing, which falls under the category of embedded systems (cs.ET).
